{
  "text": "For both digital and emerging analog accelerator approaches, the precision of the operands and operations involved in the DNN determines the accuracy, latency and energy consumption of the inference operation. In particular, for CIM architectures the precision of the DACs and ADCs involved in the operation computation greatly influences the total area and power consumption [CITATION_1] . Consequently, the quantization of both weights and activations is critical on the design of the accelerated system.",
